value.0: These are the server rules, select a category:

Agreement:
By playing Dungeon Eternal you agree to obey all rules set forth by the DM staff.
You understand and accept that the laws are in the interpretation of the DM staff and include, but are not limited, to those listed. You agree to give every DM the respect that their position deserves, and you understand that their word is law and you may be punished for going against their orders or generally disrespecting them.

* If you feel something is "too good to be true," then it IS "too good to be true." (You are welcome to ask if something is "too good" without penalty for asking, however, using something "too good to be true" without permission will result in punishment under cheating)

Definition: An insulting criticism or remark meant to incite anger.

The use of flames to incite anger in any form of chat will not be tolerated.

Use of foul language will not be tolerated in any form.

Regardless of excuse punishment must be dealt, preferably when the incident occurs.

Definition: To act dishonestly

DM interpretation: To use any knowledge that is not public or DM knowledge to gain a unfair advantage in the game.

Examples: Using a bug to get gold, XP, etc.

Definition: Treat others as you would like to be treated.

DM interpretation: Treat others as a DM would treat another DM.

- Have fun :)
- For suggestions, comments, or bug reports, please visit:

http://www.createforum.com/dungeoneternal

- Set traps
- Cast offensive spells
- Perform offensive actions

* Locking onto players is permitted *

- Abuse shout
- Harass others
- Use racial slurs
- Log out to avoid death
- Log out to avoid being pick-pocketed
- Stock inventory with useless items
Things you SHOULD NOT do in No PvP areas
